        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &quot;Livelihood Opportunity Promotion Scheme (Disabled)&quot; scheme was launched by the Social Welfare Department, Government of Uttarakhand. It aims to empower persons with disabilities by providing financial assistance for sustainable self-employment and livelihood generation. Under this scheme, the beneficiaries are supported with a mix of grants, subsidized loans, and margin money for term loans, shop construction, and bank-linked enterprises.\n",
        "benefits_md": "**Term Loan Scheme:**\n\n\n  - Project Cost: ₹75,000/-\n  - Grant: 20% or ₹10,000/-, whichever is less\n  - Term Loan: ₹65,000/- at 6% annual interest rate\n\n\n**Shop Construction Scheme:**\n\n\n  - Project Cost: ₹50,000/-\n  - Grant: 20% or ₹10,000/-, whichever is less\n  - Margin Money Loan: ₹40,000/- at 4% annual interest rate, repayable in 60 monthly installments\n\n\n**Margin Money Loan Scheme for Bank Supported Loan:**\n\n\n  - Project Cost: Up to ₹2,00,000/-\n  - Grant: 20%, maximum of ₹10,000/-\n  - Margin Money: 25% of the project cost at 4% annual interest rate, repayable in 36 monthly installments\n\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to promote self-reliance among persons with disabilities through grants, term loans, and margin money assistance.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
